title: OU picked third, OSU eighth in Big 12 women's poll
text:
Baylor picked to win Big 12 women's basketball, OU picked to finish third, OSU picked eighth THE ASSOCIATED PRESS   2:57   2:57   
Subjects: 
Oklahoma (553) 

OKLAHOMA CITY â€” Oklahoma is picked to finish third and Oklahoma State is picked eighth in the Big 12 women's basketball conference. 
Baylor is the pick to win the conference and Texas is second in a poll of conference coaches released Wednesday. Baylor received eight votes to win in the poll while Texas and OU each received one. 
Iowa State is picked fourth, followed by TCU; West Virginia; Kansas State; OSU; Texas Tech; and Kansas.
